    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="585"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.516/32.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department has received a cable from Port au Prince with request that it be
                    forwarded you, which it does, paraphrased, as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Judge of Federal authority came and verified cash, placing seals on safes
                            which contain cash as balance of retrait. Suspension of operations
                            compulsory. Shall we close bank? We wait instructions from you.
                            Government promulgated liberal issue of paper, also law authorizing
                            creation of a new bank by the Government and interior loan 1,200,000
                            gourdes guaranteed by all free duties at time of issue.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bank Haiti</hi>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
